  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Wednesday. Our class took a field trip to the zoo today, and by the end, my legs were more tired than my brain, which is rare.",
      "zh": "星期三。我們班今天去動物園校外教學，到最後我的腿比我的腦子還累，這種情況很少見。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The first exhibit was the giraffe enclosure, and honestly, nothing prepares you for how impossibly tall a giraffe actually is up close.",
      "zh": "第一個展區是長頸鹿區，老實說，沒有任何事能讓你做好心理準備，近看長頸鹿到底有多不可思議地高。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Right next to the giraffes stood a zebra, and William spent five full minutes arguing that its stripes were \"clearly hand-painted.\"",
      "zh": "長頸鹿旁邊站著一隻斑馬，William 花了整整五分鐘爭論牠的條紋「明顯是手畫上去的」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We moved on to the hippopotamus pool, where a massive hippo stayed almost completely underwater except for its eyes and nose.",
      "zh": "我們接著走到河馬池，一隻巨大的河馬幾乎整個泡在水裡，只露出眼睛和鼻子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A panda in the next section was doing absolutely nothing except eating, which several of my classmates found deeply relatable.",
      "zh": "下一區的貓熊什麼都沒做，就只是一直在吃，我好幾個同學都覺得這種狀態非常有共鳴。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Near the panda area, a camel stood perfectly still, looking unbothered by the crowd of loud, excited students pointing cameras at it.",
      "zh": "貓熊區附近，一隻駱駝一動也不動地站著，完全不受一群大聲又興奮、拿著相機猛拍的學生打擾。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The wolf enclosure was quieter than I expected; most of the wolves were resting in the shade instead of howling dramatically like in movies.",
      "zh": "狼群區比我預期的還安靜；大部分的狼都躲在樹蔭下休息，不像電影裡那樣戲劇性地嚎叫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A fox darted quickly across its enclosure, and William insisted it looked exactly like Perry, minus the ability to fetch a stick.",
      "zh": "一隻狐狸快速地穿過牠的圍欄，William 堅持說牠看起來跟 Perry 一模一樣，只是不會撿樹枝而已。"
    },
    {
      "en": "In the small mammal house, a fat, sleepy hippo statue at the entrance turned out to be fake, which disappointed at least three kids in our group.",
      "zh": "在小型哺乳動物館，入口那隻胖胖、看起來很想睡的河馬雕像其實是假的，讓我們這組至少三個小孩失望不已。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We watched keepers feed a goat and a rooster in the small farm area, where William tried to convince a staff member to let him hold a nut for the goat.",
      "zh": "我們看飼育員在小農場區餵一隻山羊和一隻公雞，William 試圖說服一位工作人員讓他拿一顆堅果餵山羊。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A quiet pond nearby held a few geese and doves, and one very determined goose chased a boy from another class all the way to the gift shop.",
      "zh": "附近一個安靜的池塘裡有幾隻鵝和鴿子，其中一隻非常有毅力的鵝，一路把另一班一個男生追到了紀念品店。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Near the aviary, an eagle sat completely still on a high branch, watching everyone below like it was personally judging our behavior.",
      "zh": "在鳥舍附近，一隻老鷹一動也不動地棲在高高的樹枝上，俯視著下面的每個人，好像在親自評判我們的行為。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A crow nearby stole a piece of bread right out of someone's hand, which Bernice called \"the most impressive crime I have ever witnessed.\"",
      "zh": "旁邊一隻烏鴉直接從某人手裡叼走了一片麵包，Bernice 說這是「我這輩子見過最厲害的犯罪行為」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The aquarium building held both a shark tank and a much bigger tank for a slow-moving whale model that turned out to just be an educational display.",
      "zh": "水族館裡有一個鯊魚缸，還有一個更大的缸，裡面是一隻慢慢移動的鯨魚模型，結果只是一個教育展示品。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A turtle in the reptile section moved so slowly across its rock that William swore it had not moved at all in the ten minutes we watched it.",
      "zh": "爬蟲區的一隻烏龜在牠的岩石上爬得超慢，William 發誓我們看的那十分鐘裡牠根本沒動過。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One older keeper, cleaning near the ape enclosure, told us the apes in his care were smarter than most of the students on this trip, which stung a little.",
      "zh": "一位年紀較大的飼育員，在猿類區附近打掃時，跟我們說他照顧的猿類比這趟校外教學裡大部分學生都還聰明，這話有點刺耳。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of the day, we had seen a giraffe, a zebra, a hippo, a panda, a camel, wolves, a fox, a goat, a rooster, geese, doves, an eagle, a crow, sharks, a whale display, a turtle, and apes, all before lunch.",
      "zh": "到了一天結束，我們在午餐前就已經看完了長頸鹿、斑馬、河馬、貓熊、駱駝、狼群、狐狸、山羊、公雞、鵝、鴿子、老鷹、烏鴉、鯊魚、鯨魚展示、烏龜，還有猿類。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: a zoo trip is basically a very long roll call of animals, and somehow William still wanted to see \"one more thing\" at every single exhibit.",
      "zh": "今日心得：動物園校外教學基本上就是一場超級冗長的動物點名，而 William 不知怎麼地，在每一個展區都還想再多看「一個東西」。"
    }
  ],
